-- Bernanke's testimony on Fed's liquidity efforts
-- 
-- Tue Feb 10, 2009 2:18pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/02/10/us-financial-bailout-highlights-sb-idUSTRE5196C620090210

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The following are highlights of Federal Reserve Chairman Ben Bernanke's testimony on Tuesday to the House of Representatives Financial Services Committee on the Fed's efforts to foster liquidity in financial markets. 

 BERNANKE ON TOO BIG TO FAIL: "Too big to fail is an enormous problem. We are very unhappy with this problem, and we think it should be a top priority to fix it as we go forward so that this situation doesn't arise again. BERNANKE ON RESPONSE TO FED EFFORTS "We have been encouraged by the responses to these programs, including the reports and evaluations offered by market participants and analysts. Notably, our lending to financial institutions, together with actions taken by other agencies, has helped to relax the severe liquidity strains experienced by many firms and has been associated with considerable improvements in interbank lending markets." BERNANKE ON FED BALANCE SHEET "95 percent, the bulk of our lending ... are extremely safe, they are overcollateralized." "That would (be loans that are safe) ... $1.9 trillion, that's correct. The other $100 billion, which is related to the Bear Stearns and AIG operations is a bit less secure, although our anticipation is that we will not lose money on those..."